    "long_instructions": "### Changing Beats\r\n\r\nYou're going to create a backing track that feels dynamic and interesting by changing up the beat, bass, and lead patterns. Here's how:\r\n\r\n- Each sound (beat, bass, and lead) will follow its own pattern for how often it changes.\r\n- To make it all work together, you'll need to use a nested loop (a loop inside another loop).\r\n\r\n**Here's what each sound should do:**\r\n\r\n- **Beat:** Use 4 different beats. Each beat plays once, then move to the next one. After all 4 have played, start over.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/bbf600788d44ef67362449935d228c8f-image-1745271174695.png)\r\n\r\n- **Bass:** Use 3 different bass patterns. Each one plays twice before switching. After all 3 have played twice, start over.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/68220b65f5a3dbc1deda6ff694d397b1-image-1745271115774.png)\r\n\r\n- **Lead:** Use 2 different lead sounds. Each one plays three times before switching. After both have played three times, start over.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/0c17fea82d54ee3789631e228d342ea8-image-1745271150775.png)\r\n\r\n- All of these should play together!\r\n- Make sure the total loop lasts at least 24 measures before it repeats.\r\n\r\nUse Live Coding to change the tracks that aren't playing so when the cycle restarts, it sounds different!\r\n\r\n::: details [**Want an additional hint? Click here**]\r\n\r\nHere is what the final code could look like:\r\n![](https://images.code.org/bd1d37c46903cd4abc1e27eececf24e3-image-1750964279964.png)\r\n:::",
